Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MSCs) have gained high attention as they offer a possibility to utilize solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) in mobile applications such as auxiliary power units in heavy duty vehicles.
Titulo: Novel processing of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for metal-supported fuel cells

Sentencas: Cathode reliability is one of the main issues of MSC development, since cathodes tend to degrade rapidly after being in-situ activated during onset of the stack operation.
Titulo: Novel processing of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for metal-supported fuel cells

Sentencas: In the present study, a novel sintering route for La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathode material was developed.
Titulo: Novel processing of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for metal-supported fuel cells

Sentencas: Sintering of the screen printed cathodes was performed before stack operation at 950 degrees C in reducing Ar atmosphere for 3 h. Under these conditions, severe oxidation of the metallic substrate and the Ni in the anode was avoided reliably.
Titulo: Novel processing of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for metal-supported fuel cells

Sentencas: For proof of concept, phase stability and microstructure of the MSC Cathodes were characterized.
Titulo: Novel processing of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for metal-supported fuel cells

Sentencas: The results reveal that cathode layers sintered in Ar exhibit substantially unproved adherence and mechanical stability compared to conventionally processed MSC cathodes, making them ready for systematic investigation of electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Novel processing of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for metal-supported fuel cells
